I can't help myself.
Whenever I go here, it's because I'm dying to go here for one thing: the vegan "shredded pork" with vermicelli and some "pork" eggrolls.
So, I can't tell you about lots of menu items.
I CAN tell you that this one is delicious.
Hue Thai has standard meaty Vietnamese fare: noodles soups, banh mi, bun, etc.
And for the adventurous meaties, you can get tripe and blood cubes and all the extra parts.
But I can't rate how that tastes!
I can say that they have a fairly large vegan/veggie menu with faux meats (I've tried the pork, which appears to be shredded tofu and the lemongrass chicken - ok, gluten-based).
You can even get faux pho with a variety of fake meats, but I was not impressed.
The broth had no flavour at all to me.
They also have all the standard boba-fiable drinks, most of which can be made with soy milk.
Reasonably priced, fairly fast service, and close to Ronald's Donuts!!
