I read reviews that the bread is what sets Hue Thai's from Lee's or other places.
I ordered the House Special (Banh Mi Dat Biet) and the Pork (Bahn Mi Thit Nuong).Maybe I came at a bad time, the bread wasn't stale or hard, but I didn't think it was soft, either.
Definitely tasty, though, I'll give them that.
The fillings were delicious, too.
